25|$|Over 98% of Fannie's {{loans were}} paying timely during 2008. Both Fannie and Freddie had {{positive}} net worth as of {{the date of the}} takeover, meaning the value of their assets exceeded their liabilities. However, Fannie's total assets to capital (leverage ratio) was about 20:1, while Freddie's was about 70:1. These numbers increase significantly if one includes all the mortgage-backed <b>assets</b> they <b>guaranteed.</b> These ratios are considerably higher than investment banks, which leverage around 30:1.|$|R
