40|$|Current {{maintenance}} {{policies are}} time oriented and still based on expected cost or availability optimization {{rather than being}} optimized with risk-cost considerations. Maintenance managers look continuously for the way to improve the availability of their production machines in order to assure given production throughputs. They want {{to achieve this goal}} at the lowest expenditure. One of their major concerns is then budget allocation. They are willing to spend money if the reliability improvement of their <b>assets</b> is <b>guaranteed.</b> This paper proposes {{a new version of the}} modified bloc replacement strategy (MBRP) with a risk-cost consideration. We analyze the impact of this maintenance strategy for a single component system for various risk level. We highlight the impact of the decision maker's acceptable risk levels on the scheduled dates of preventive maintenance activities...|$|R
