40|$|Abstract: GAP (<b>Guaranteed</b> <b>Asset</b> Protection) {{insurance}} is an insurance product that insures the difference (if any) between the loan balance {{and the actual}} value of the underlying asset. Typically, this {{insurance is}} sold {{in conjunction with a}} traditional insurance product and guarantees that an insurable event will be sufficient to satisfy any lien upon the asset. While this type of insurance is used to cover a variety of exposures, the largest asset class is private passenger vehicles...|$|R
